KANO – President Muhammadu Buhari’s convoy came under attack earlier on Monday in Kano State. (See photos and videos). The President is in the North West state to commission some projects executed by the government of Abdullahi Ganduje. However, as the president was making its way to Hotoro area of Kano state, angry youths pelted the convoy with stones and made further attempt to bring down one of the helicopters in the president’s convoy.